snippet.title: GROOM, GINAYUMA RAW NI BRIDE?!
snippet.description:
⚠️PARA SA INYONG MGA SUMBONG AT REKLAMO ⚠️

Maaari po kayong magtungo sa ACTION CENTER ng RAFFY TULFO IN ACTION sa TV5 Media Center, Reliance Cor. Sheridan St., Mandaluyong mul a 9:00AM-3:00PM, tuwing Lunes hanggang Biyernes. Mangyari lamang po na magdala ng vaccination card at huwag nang magsama ng bata. Kung kayo naman ay senior citizen o may karamdaman, magpadala na lamang po kayo ng inyong representative sa aming tanggapan. Gaya po ng aming paalala, LIBRE at WALA PONG BAYAD ang serbisyong aming ibinibigay kaya 'wag na 'wag po kayong magpapaloko sa mga scammers na mangangako na pauunahin kayo sa pila at maniningil ng bayad.

#RTIA #TULFO #IDOLRAFFY  #WANTEDSARADYO
#SUMBONGATAKSYON #RAFFYTULFO #RAFFY #TULFO #RAFFYTULFOINACTION #WSR #TULFOLIVE

snippet.title: China Slams ICC Over Duterte Arrest Warrant, Warns Against ‘Double Standards’
snippet.description:
China Slams ICC Over Duterte Arrest Warrant, Warns Against ‘Double Standards’

China’s foreign ministry announced that it was closely monitoring the situation after the Philippines arrested its former president, Rodrigo Duterte. The arrest, which came on a warrant issued by the International Criminal Court, marks a significant development in the ongoing ICC investigation into alleged crimes against humanity. During a regular press briefing, Chinese spokesperson Mao Ning addressed the situation, responding to questions about Duterte’s arrest. Duterte, a former mayor and prosecutor who served as president of the Philippines from 2016 to 2022, was taken into custody early on Tuesday. This marks the biggest step yet in the ICC’s investigation into Duterte’s controversial anti-drug crackdown, which led to thousands of deaths and widespread international condemnation. After his arrest, Duterte was sent to The Hague, where he is expected to arrive on the morning of March 12. At 79 years old, Duterte could become the first Asian former head of state to stand trial at the International Criminal Court

snippet.title: Is Rodrigo Duterte Facing Death Penalty Or Life Behind Bars as ICC War on Drugs Case Heats Up
snippet.description:
Rodrigo Duterte Arrest: Former Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte faces potential life imprisonment if convicted by the International Criminal Court (ICC) for crimes against humanity due to his controversial war on drugs, which critics claim led to thousands of extrajudicial killings. Although Duterte’s legal team will mount defenses, the threat of a prison sentence is real. The ICC can impose sentences up to 30 years, and appeals are possible. This legal battle is ongoing, with global attention on the outcome.

snippet.title: “Double standards…” China warns ICC against ‘politicizing’ Philippines ex-president Duterte’s arrest
snippet.description:
On March 11, China’s foreign ministry announced that it was closely monitoring the situation after the Philippines arrested its former president, Rodrigo Duterte. The arrest, which came on a warrant issued by the International Criminal Court, marks a significant development in the ongoing ICC investigation into alleged crimes against humanity. During a regular press briefing, Chinese spokesperson Mao Ning addressed the situation, responding to questions about Duterte’s arrest. Duterte, a former mayor and prosecutor who served as president of the Philippines from 2016 to 2022, was taken into custody early on Tuesday. This marks the biggest step yet in the ICC’s investigation into Duterte’s controversial anti-drug crackdown, which led to thousands of deaths and widespread international condemnation. After his arrest, Duterte was sent to The Hague, where he is expected to arrive on the morning of March 12. At 79 years old, Duterte could become the first Asian former head of state to stand trial at the International Criminal Court.

#China #Philippines #Duterte

snippet.title: Old Lady Thought She Was Being Robbed! But the Guys Had Good Intentions! #shorts
snippet.description: What started as a scary moment for this elderly lady turned into the most heartwarming surprise! When three young boys on bikes approached her and grabbed her bag, she feared the worst. But instead of stealing from her, they filled her bag with groceries, leaving her in tears of gratitude. Watch till the end to see how kindness can truly change someone's day!

snippet.title: Prison Chef’s Birthday Wish Comes True with a Surprise Burger #shorts
snippet.description: A prison chef dreamed of a tasty burger for his birthday, but the prison food was unbearable. Seeing his disappointment, his cellmate gathered ingredients from other inmates to surprise him. The chef prepared a delicious burger and even lit a simple candle. Just then, a guard arrived with a special "Happy Birthday" decoration. Overwhelmed with gratitude, the chef shared his burger with everyone, proving that kindness exists even behind bars.

snippet.title: As it happened: The arrest of Rodrigo Duterte | ABS-CBN News
snippet.description:
Former President Rodrigo Duterte was arrested by police officers on Tuesday (March 11) acting on a warrant from the International Criminal Court (ICC) over his war on drugs, shortly after he arrived in the Philippines from Hong Kong.
Duterte, 79, faces a charge of "the crime against humanity of murder", according to the ICC, for the crackdown in which rights groups estimate tens of thousands of mostly poor men were killed by officers and vigilantes, often without proof they were linked to drugs.
Here are key moments of the arrest on Tuesday morning.

snippet.title: Torre on Kitty cursing, Honeylet refusing flight, blocking Sara's entry | ABS-CBN News
snippet.description:
Police Criminal Investigation and Detection Group Director Major General Nicolas Torre on Thursday (March 13) gave details of the arrest of Rodrigo Duterte, including his interactions with the former president's family members. Speaking with ABS-CBN News, he addressed being cursed by Duterte's daughter Kitty, revealed that Duterte's partner Honeylet Avanceña was offered a seat on the flight to The Hague, and confirmed that he ordered to not allow Vice President Sara Duterte into Villamor Air Base.

snippet.description:
#露兮粑粑#萌娃#可爱#云养娃
欢迎来到“露兮粑粑”频道，这里是记录萌娃，即人类幼崽成长的温馨家园。
